[2] Australia (New South Wales) warning
Date: Thu 5 Jan 2017
Source: News.com.au, Daily Telegraph report [edited]
http://www.news.com.au/national/nsw-act/measles-warning-for-sydney-after-infectious-passenger-arrives/news-story/003cf53cf40138f8a775958b020db14b


Measles warning for Sydney after infectious passenger arrives
-------------------------------------------------------------
Measles' symptoms include fever, sore eyes and a cough followed 3 or 4 days later by a red, blotchy rash.

Sydney residents are being urged to watch for symptoms of measles after an infected passenger arrived in the city from a flight from Bali [Indonesia] on New Year's Day [1 Jan 2017]. NSW [New South Wales] Health said the young woman arrived in Sydney on Virgin Australia Airlines flight VA 70 from Denpasar, Bali about 7.40am.

While still infectious, she visited Sutherland Hospital's emergency department on 4 Jan [2017]. There is a chance she may have exposed people to the disease during her stay here, but the case is not linked to the cluster of measles cases in Sydney last month [December 2016]. - ... more

