[Because of the highly contagious nature of measles, even though the disease is rare in Australia, introduction from outside the country to unvaccinated individuals always presents a threat. And once in the country, the virus has the potential to spread rapidly. Thus it is important to maintain immunization by vaccination of children with 2 doses of MMR vaccine. See previous posts for discussion of MMR vaccine.

