[See ProMED-mail post Measles update (01): USA (CA), Sudan (SK) 20170103.4740174, which discusses the spread to Santa Barbara from Los Angeles (California, USA). It only takes one infected individual to come into contact with unvaccinated, non-immune individuals, to start spread of measles virus in a community. This places children, especially those with underlying health conditions, at serious risk.

See the location of California in the United States at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4747028,106. - Mod.LK]
